<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Grachev: Sevastopol Needed as Fleet's `Main Base' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev: Sevastopol Needed as Fleet's `Main Base' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005220194 </F>
<F P=103> LD1005220194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Moscow Radio Moscow in Russian to 
Tajikistan at 1700 GMT on 10 May in the "Slavyanka" program of 
the Russian Defense Ministry carries a feature on the 
anniversary of the liberation of Sevastopol in World War II. 
Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev is quoted on the future 
status of the port: 
  Grachev says: "Sevastopol should be the main base of 
Russia's 
Black Sea Fleet. We consider that in addition to Sevastopol, 
the fleet should also be based in Balaklava, Feodosiya, Kerch, 
and Donuzlav where the main forces of Russia's Black Sea Fleet 
are deployed and also where units and formations are stationed. 
It is clear that we do not have the right to, and we will not 
undermine the combat readiness of the Black Sea Fleet, a 
battle-worthy and full-blooded formation of the Russian 
Federation Armed Forces, as this would create a real threat to 
the security of Russia in this region. Nor do we have the right 
to worsen the already difficult social position of many Black 
Sea sailors." 

</TEXT>

