<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Established for Trade With Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Established for Trade With Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005151394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1337 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1005151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A government commission led by Russian Vice-Premier 
Aleksandr Shokhin was formed in Russia for talks on economic 
cooperation and trade with Crimea. This was said in Simferopol 
on Tuesday at a session of the Crimean parliament by Chairman of 
the Russian state Duma Committee for CIS Konstantin Zatulin. In 
his words, in the near future "a Crimean-Russian 
interparliamentary group" is also expected to be formed. 
  Zatulin pointed out that "today there is a possibility to 
start a new history of Crimea." At the same time, he urged 
Crimean parliamentarians "to be more contained and to take 
balanced decisions needed for the prosperity of the Crimean 
Republic." 

</TEXT>

