<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian, French Paratroops To Hold Joint Exercises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian, French Paratroops To Hold Joint Exercises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105104294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0924 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Vlasov] </F>
  [Text] Pskov May 11 TASS -- A delegation of French military 
officials arrived by plane here on Tuesday evening to 
familiarize themselves with the way of life of servicemen of the 
Pskov Airborne Infantry Division. 
  They will visit the Division's quarters on Wednesday. 
  Lieutenant Colonel Viktor Sorokin, chief of the Russian 
airborne infantry forces, is accompanying the French delegation. 
  Sorokin and Major General Ivan Babichev, commander of the 
Pskov division in question, will do parachute jumps from an 
IL-76 assault aircraft on May 12. 
  In June, 90 French paratroopers from an airborne infantry 
regiment stationed near the town of Castres are to come here to 
participate in a joint exercise with the Russian counterparts. 
They will stay here for ten days. 
  Simultaneously, 90 Russian paratroopers from the Pskov 
Airborne Infantry Division will take part in a joint exercise in 
France. 

</TEXT>

