<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soviet Weaponry Reportedly Being Used in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soviet Weaponry Reportedly Being Used in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005222494 Moscow Radio Moscow in Russian to Tajikistan 
1700 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1005222494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Moscow Radio Moscow in Russian to 
Tajikistan at 1700 GMT on 10 May, in a broadcast from the 
"Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense Ministry, reports 
that weapons which the USSR used to supply to Yemen are now 
being used in the current fighting. 
  The unidentified announcer says: "In Yemen there are now 
over 1,000 of our tanks. These are T-62, T-55, and T-54 models. 
In Yemen at present there are about 800 Soviet-made artillery 
combat vehicles and armored transporters. There are tens of our 
aircraft -- Su-22, MiG-21, and MiG-23, and even 
surface-to-surface missiles, Scud, and SS-21 missiles. The 
Yemenis also have some of our Mi-8 and Mi-24 combat helicopters 
and our combat vessels." "Slavyanka" will report on how these 
weapons perform. 

</TEXT>

