<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Plans To Deliver Aid to Rwandan Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Plans To Deliver Aid to Rwandan Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105130094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1152 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Marina Ryklina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- A group of experts from the 
Russian Ministry for Emergencies flew to the Tanzanian capital 
of Dar es Salaam on Wednesday. At the request of the office of 
the U.N supreme commissioner for refugees, Russia will 
participate in the operation to provide those who are fleeing 
the bloodsoaked Rwanda with humanitarian aid. 
  According to a spokesman for the Russian Ministry for 
Emergencies, the experts will examine the routes and conditions 
for Russian drivers who are expected to deliver foodstuffs and 
medicines for Rwandan refugees. 
  The Russian transport team has already worked in the former 
Yugoslavia. However, the tropical climate, health hazards, 
difficulties with the delivery of heavy-duty Kamaz trucks by air 
and unloading them require specific preparations. 
  The Russian drivers are expected to start the deliveries 
this 
month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

