<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, 3 Others Register as Presidential Candidates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk, 3 Others Register as Presidential Candidates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005133494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1302 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1005133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko, Mikhail Moroz] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 10 May TASS -- Four candidates for the post of 
Ukrainian president have become known here on Tuesday, including 
Leonid Kravchuk. The other candidates include socialist leader 
Aleksandr Moroz, president of the Ukrainian Union of 
Industrialists and Businessmen Leonid Kuchma, and Parliament 
Speaker Ivan Plush, ITAR-TASS was told by vice-chairman of the 
Ukrainian Central Elections Commissions Valentin Kirnenko. He 
noted that all the candidates, according to preliminary 
information, had collected the 100,000 signatures, required to 
be registered as presidential candidate. 
  According to the same source, two would-be candidates have 
asked the central commission to give them more time to collect 
the needed signatures, but were refused. According to the 
legislation in force, a presidential candidate had to collect 
the needed signatures before 6 May. Moreover, he had to collect 
100,000 "autographs" in 18 regions and not less than 1,500 in 
each of them. 
  Leader of one of the Ukrainian Rukh organisations Larisa 
Skorik voluntarily gave up the race. According to some reports, 
she plans to campaign for Leonid Kravchuk. The Ukrainian 
president still wants the presidential elections to be put off 
to a later date. In addition to a large group of MP's [members 
of parliament], his stand is backed by the right-wing centrist 
parties and movements. Kravchuk plans to hold a closed meeting 
with them today. It is not difficult to guess that they will 
work out the tactics and strategy for the session of the new 
Ukrainian parliament, which is to open on 11 May. 

</TEXT>

