<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean Group Supports Ukrainian Statehood </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Group Supports Ukrainian Statehood </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905220894 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2100 GMT 9 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0905220894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 9 May -- An extended assembly of the 
coordinating council of the Congress of Ukrainians of Crimea has 
taken place. Representatives of the peninsula's democratic 
parties, civil organizations, and movements took part. They 
decided to form a parliamentary type representative body of the 
nationalist democratic forces of with a state orientation: the 
Ukrainian Civil Council of Crimea [Ukrayinska hromadyanska rada 
Krymu]. The newly formed organization aims to guarantee the 
inviolability of Ukraine's borders, the protection and 
strengthening of Ukrainian statehood in Crimea, and maintaining 
political stability peace and inter-ethnic accord on the 
peninsula. 
  The participants of the assembly were motivated to form such 
a body by the deepening crisis of Crimea's bodies of power 
which, in the opinion of the autonomy's representatives of the 
national democrats, has recently acquired a dangerous 
characteristic. 

</TEXT>

