<F P=103> LD1005190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new composition of deputies of Ukraine's Supreme 
Council will begin its work on 11 May. An agreement on creating 
a parliamentary centrist bloc was approved at a meeting of 
leaders of several deputies' groups and factions. This was 
stated by Vyacheslav Chornovil, head of the Rukh group in the 
Supreme Council, at a news conference in Kiev on 10 May. He 
noted that representatives of the "Tsentr" [Center] group, the 
Rukh group, "Derzhavnist" [Statehood], and "Za Reformy Dlya 
Narodu" [in Support of Reforms for the People] had joined the 
bloc. Chornovil stressed that a meeting of the bloc will 
discuss the groups' positions on basic issues, which are to be 
submitted for parliament's consideration. 

