  [Text] The Belarusian Trade Union Federation has received 
an answer to its appeal -- containing a proposal to adopt a 
decision on a date for early Supreme Soviet elections -- to 
Supreme Soviet Chairman Mechyslaw Hryb. The answer reads: The 
issue has been discussed by the Supreme Soviet Commission for 
State-Building. A decision to shift the discussion of the draft 
law on introducing changes and addenda to the Law of the 
Republic of Belarus on Electing People's Deputies was adopted 
during a regular meeting of the 13th session. Together with the 
discussion of this draft law, a draft resolution on fixing a 
date for Belarusian Supreme Soviet elections will be discussed. 
It will include a date for these elections, the answer reads. 
As for the opening date of the regular session, it is unlikely 
that it will be held before we learn the name of the first 
Belarusian president. This will probably [words indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

