<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akayev Sets Up Commission on Insolvent Enterprises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Akayev Sets Up Commission on Insolvent Enterprises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105123494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1109 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kyrgyz President Askar Akayev has issued a decree on 
the state commission for reorganization and liquidation of 
insolvent enterprises. This was announced to INTERFAX by the 
Kyrgyz president's press service. 
  The same source told INTERFAX that this had been done in 
order to eliminate broke enterprises, to make the state budget 
healthy, to achieve financial stabilization in Kyrgyzstan and to 
carry out structural reorganization. 
  The commission will be headed by Kyrgyz Premier Apas 
Jumagulov and will include the chairperson of the national bank, 
the finance minister and others. 
  The commission will focus on implementation of programs 
concerning unprofitable enterprises. The presidential decree 
must be implemented within a month. 

</TEXT>

