<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenian Attacks Break Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Attacks Break Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1105175494 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1105175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Despite the declaration of a cease-fire as of 0000 
on 9 May, the Armenian side launched new combat operations in 
the Agdamskiy Rayon sector of the front line at 0900 today. 
Following a preparatory artillery bombardment, the enemy 
attacked Akhmadagaly in Agdamskiy Rayon. Armored vehicles 
supported the onslaught. Violent clashes are taking place 
around that town at the present time. 
  Uninterrupted positional fighting has continued in 
Gorenboyskiy, Terterskiy, and Fizulinskiy Rayons during the past 
two days. The Armenians suffered many casualties in their 
unsuccessful attacks against Gorenboy. The enemy units lost 
more than 50 men. They abandoned 12 machine guns and grenade 
launchers and fled from the battlefield. 
  The border observation posts in Kedabekskiy Rayon were fired 
on from Armenia last night. The enemy also fired on our 
positions in the Omer Pass region in the northern part of 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayon. 

</TEXT>

