<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Forces Resume Attacks on Terter, Agdam </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1105160494 Baku AZERTAC in English 1522 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1105160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERTAC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] The Armenian forces 
resumed their attempts to fight their way through the 
Azerbaijani Armed Forces defences to Terter and Agdam in the 
morning. According to the Defence Ministry of Azerbaijan, 10 
Armenian soldiers died and one tank became a casualty as a 
result of the fighting continued in the afternoon. 
  The Azerbaijani Army forced the Armenian Armed Forces to 
retreat to their starting battle lines as a result of the heavy 
fighting taken place near the village of Kichik Akhmadagali in 
the district of Agdamskiy. Both the sides have suffered losses. 
More than 40 Armenian soldiers were killed, while the 
Azerbaijani side suffered 10 casualties. The enemy's three 
tanks and one vehicle gasoline tanker became casualties. 
  Regiments of the Azerbaijani Army were subject to heavy 
artillery shelling in Geranboy and Kelbajar. 

</TEXT>

