<F P=102>   LD1105205594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1853 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Sevindzh Abdullayeva and </F>
Viktor Shulman] 
  [Text] Baku 11 May TASS--The parliament and government of 
the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic of Azerbaijan issued an 
ultimatum to the local section of the Popular Front on Wednesday 
[11 May], demanding it to stop unlawful actions aimed at 
destabilising the situation in the Ordubad District of the 
Republic. 
  The Nakhichevan authorities also said that they will appeal 
to Azerbaijani President Heydar Aliyev to impose a state of 
emergency in the region if the situation is not normalised 
within three days. 
  The situation in the district, home base of ex-President 
Abulfaz Elchibey, worsened two days ago, following the 
appointment of a new head of the administration. Several local 
leaders and deputies refused to obey the new head and called on 
their supporters to follow their suit. 
  A group of front activists tried to seize the building of 
the 
local executive council last night. As a result of a clash with 
the police, several people were injured. 

