<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "International Economic Relations Are </F>
Expanding"] 
  [Text] Our republic will be one of the participants in the 
first session of the International Committee for International 
Cooperation and Economic Reform, which is to take place on 12-14 
May. On the agenda of the first session is discussion of the 
issue of the production and distribution of foodstuffs; 
cooperation in the fuel and energy and banking and finance 
spheres; ensuring social protection of the population during the 
period of economic reforms; and other issues. Our country will 
be represented at the session by a group of experts headed by 
Azerbaijani Minister of the Economy S. Sadygov. Let us recall 
that this organization was founded on 1 February 1994 and unites 
18 countries of the former USSR, as well as Central and East 
Europe. Its headquarters are located in the capital of the FRG. 

