<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Denies Georgian Armed Groups in Gali Rayon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Denies Georgian Armed Groups in Gali Rayon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105203794 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1800 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Press Service of the Georgian </F>
Defense Ministry on 11 May] 
  [Text] The Georgian Defense Ministry Press Service made the 
following statement: Russia's Ostankino television program, 
Novosti, based on Abkhaz sources, on 10 May, in effect, 
broadcast misinformation alleging the entry of Georgian armed 
groups into the Gali rayon. The same source asserts that 250 
armed Georgian fighters are operating in the Gali rayon. 
  The Press Service of the Georgian Defense Ministry is 
authorized to state that this news does not correspond to the 
truth. Similar information, based on Abkhaz sources, has been 
broadcast many times before. In this particular case, it aims 
at a specific target -- to separate or wreck Georgian-Abkhaz 
talks on peaceful settlement that started today in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

