<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conscription for Russian Border Troops Begins </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1105153094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 11 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1105153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Vitaliy Denisov report from Tbilisi under the "News" </F>
rubric: "Georgian Guys Like Russian "Green Caps"] 
  [Text] Conscription of Georgian personnel for the Russian 
border troops on Georgian territory has begun according to an 
agreement between Georgia and Russia on the joint protection of 
borders. 
  Colonel Vladimir Berezin, deputy chief of the "Gruziya" 
["Georgia"] group of forces of the Caucasus Special Border 
District, said that at the initial stage Georgian citizens will 
account for 10 percent of the group's strength -- in May-June 
350 young Georgians will be conscripted into the Russian border 
units. In the future, the entire length of the Georgian-Turkish 
border will be protected by Georgian units. 

