<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ulmanis Calls Saeima Presidium Session to Discuss Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ulmanis Calls Saeima Presidium Session to Discuss Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105133694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1200 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, as proposed by State President Guntis 
Ulmanis, there was an extraordinary session of the Saeima 
Presidium. The president requested a second debate on the law 
on local authorities adopted on 5 May. Ulmanis regards as 
unacceptable the provisions of paragraph 93 of the law, which 
allows for the dismissal or removal of an elected official from 
his post by the sole personal order of a minister. In his 
opinion, only the Cabinet of Ministers can dismiss or remove an 
elected official from his post. 
  The Saeima Presidium agreed to a second debate of the law on 
local authorities, allowing the Commission on State and Local 
Administration and the Judicial Commission to rule that the 
Commission of State and Local Administration will assemble the 
proposals received and prepare the laws adopted together with 
the proposals for a second debate in a plenary session of the 
Saeima. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

