<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Details Requested From Russia of Military Sites </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105201494 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, the Latvian Bureau for Monitoring the 
Withdrawal of the Russian Army presented a request to the 
headquarters of the Northwestern Group of Russian Forces to 
inform the bureau about the schedules for withdrawing from those 
Russian military sites that are not mentioned on the schedule 
for troop withdrawal presented by Russia. Ilgonis Upmalis, the 
head of the bureau, says the schedule provided by Russia does 
not include 13 Russian military sites in Latvia, nor 26 army 
units located on warships and submarines in Riga and Liepaja. 
Upmalis also requested the leaders of the Northwestern Group of 
Forces to show the numbers and addresses of the military units 
mentioned in the schedule, as well as providing lists of the 
military personnel at the army units and their family members. 
  The schedule for troop withdrawal provided by Russia is an 
appendix to the treaty signed in Moscow on the withdrawal of 
Russian troops from Latvia. 

</TEXT>

