<H3> <TI>   Baltic Defense Ministers Sign Accord With France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baltic Defense Ministers Sign Accord With France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105143694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1400 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Baltic states are strengthening military 
cooperation with Western European countries. Today in Paris the 
defense ministers of the three Baltic countries signed a 
cooperation agreement with France on defense issues. The 
document was signed by Estonian Defense Minister Indrek Kannik, 
Latvian Defense Minister Valdis Pavlovskis, and Lithuanian 
Defense Minister Linas Linkevicius. On behalf of France the 
agreement was signed by Defense Minister Francois Leotard. 
  According to the agreement, France will help the Baltic 
states to run joint military exercises, exchange officers and 
military observers, and train military personnel, including the 
Baltic peacekeeping battalion. According to the French defense 
minister, all three Baltic countries need military hardware, 
vehicles first and foremost. 
  After signing the agreement, Indrek Kannik said that the 
agreement concluded in France will help Estonia in persuading 
Russia to withdraw its troops from Estonia. 

</TEXT>

