<H3> <TI>   Kazakh, Kyrgyz, Uzbek Security Departments To Cooperate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazakh, Kyrgyz, Uzbek Security Departments To Cooperate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205054694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0427 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205054694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kulagin] </F>
  [Text] Almaty May 12 TASS -- The Kazakh State Committee for 
National Security, the Uzbek Security Service and the Kyrgyz 
State Committee for National Security signed a tripartite 
agreement on cooperation and interaction on technical provision 
of the security services of the three countries on principles of 
mutual payments. 
  The sides outlined concrete ways to carry out their plans, 
develop coordination and interaction and exercise manoeuvres by 
means of forces and technical facilities available. 
  Apart from this agreement, the Kazakh and Kyrgyz security 
departments signed and agreement on cooperation in military 
counter-intelligence. 

