<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Signed on Direct Hot Line to Bonn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement Signed on Direct Hot Line to Bonn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105140594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1327 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, 11 May (ITAR-TASS) -- A direct, scrambled 
telephone line will be set up in the nearest future between the 
Kremlin and the federal chancellor's department. An agreement 
on this was signed in Bonn today during the official visit of 
Russian Federation President Boris Yeltsin to the FRG. The 
document was signed by Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev for 
Russia and by FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel for Germany. 
  "Taking account of the mutual interest in creating the 
technical wherewithal to hold confidential telephone 
conversations at the highest level," the agreement provides for, 
"as soon as technically feasible," setting up a direct scrambled 
telephone link between the Kremlin and the federal chancellor's 
department, using two channels laid along geographically 
separate routes. 
  The agreement comes into force on the day on which it is 
signed. 

</TEXT>

