<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kohl Hold News Conference on Results of Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kohl Hold News Conference on Results of Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leaders Agree on Troop Farewell Ceremony in Berlin </H4>

<F P=102> LD1105181694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1656 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents] </F>
  [Text] Bonn May 11 TASS -- "We have agreed to see off the 
Russian troops (from Germany) in a worthy manner and add festive 
character to the event", Russian President Boris Yeltsin told a 
press conference on Wednesday adding that he and Chancellor 
Helmut Kohl had discussed the issue in detail. 
  Kohl earlier said the farewell ceremony would take place in 
Berlin where the Second World War ended. 
  The ceremony should signal an end to a certain historical 
phase, according to Yeltsin. Germany, Russia and the whole of 
Europe are entering a new era of relations, an era of 
reconciliation, he said and added that the ceremony would be a 
prologue for the celebrations of the 50th anniversary of the end 
of World War Two to be marked in 1995. 
  Yeltsin stressed that Kohl had confirmed the German position 
to politicallly include Russia into the G-7, to accept it into 
the Council of Europe and to promote an early partnership and 
cooperation agreement between Russia and the EU [European Union]. 

</TEXT>

