<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kohl Hold News Conference on Results of Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kohl Hold News Conference on Results of Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Yeltsin Says Germany Major Economic Partner </H4>

<F P=102> LD1105203194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1941 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Bonn May 11 TASS--"Germany remains Russia's major 
foreign economic partner," Russian President Boris Yeltsin told 
a joint news conference he gave here together with German 
Chancellor Helmut Kohl on Wednesday. He reported that "issues 
of economic cooperation were also in the focus of attention at 
today's talks in Bonn". 
  Under conditions of a complicated transition period Russia 
is 
presently going trough, it is difficult to avoid certain decline 
in economic ties. "Moreover, most far-sighted economic partners 
do not scale down their activity despite the temporary 
difficulties confronting Russia. I am confident that we will 
manage to overcome them", the president stressed. 
  "During the talks, we agreed to pay most attention to such 
fields of cooperation as power engineering, machine-building, 
conversion, support of small and medium-sized business, 
especially in the production sphere. We suggested using such 
effective instrument of economic relations as non-interest 
bearing commercial credit, or the so-called `swing'", Yeltsin 
said, adding that "the discussion of trade and economic 
relations between Russia and Germany will be continued on the 
second day of his visit". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

