<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Supports Russian Integration With Democratic States </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Supports Russian Integration With Democratic States </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105202494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1939 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Bonn May 11 -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl said 
today that Germany will discuss the possibility of providing 
further support to Russia and promoting its integration into the 
world economy at the forthcoming group of seven ("G-7") 
industrial leading countries of the world summit scheduled to be 
held in Naples (Italy) in July. Kohl was speaking at a supper 
hosted by him in honour of Russian President Boris Yeltsin at 
the Petersberg Government Residency today. 
  The chancellor emphasised that the German people are for new 
democratic Russia's integration into the circle of democratic 
industrial states. This is the reason why the Germans favoured 
Russia's inclusion, as broadly as possible, into the political 
part of the "G-7" summit, he said. According to him, Germany's 
Western partners expect from Russia constructive cooperation in 
settling European and international crises. 
  Helmut Kohl recalled that the last of the Russian troops 
will 
leave the German territory in August this year. "This will not 
only be drawing a line under the post-war history of Europe. We 
are united in saying that this gives our countries a special 
opportunity for strengthening and widening new friendship and 
partnership. That is why we wish to mark the withdrawal of 
Russian military personnel together in a solemn and fitting 
form," he said. 

</TEXT>

