<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns Muslim Attack on Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Condemns Muslim Attack on Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105170594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1526 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 11 May -- A Russian Foreign Ministry 
spokesman today condemned the actions of Bosnian Muslims in the 
vicinity of Brcko in the north east of Bosnia and Herzegovina. 
According to UN observers, on the morning of 10 May the Bosnian 
Army, the Russian Foreign Ministry statement notes, fired 
mortars at the central part of the city of Brcko, which is under 
Bosnian Serb control. There are dead and wounded among its 
civilian population. 
  The provocative actions by the Muslim side in what is 
currently the most explosive region of Bosnia and Herzegovina, 
carried out, moreover, on the eve of the Geneva meeting on 
achieving a Bosnian settlement, could lead to the gravest 
consequences, the Foreign Ministry spokesman pointed out. In 
condemning this action Russia insistently calls on all the sides 
involved in the Bosnian conflict to show maximum restraint and 
self-control at this crucial moment. It is time finally to 
discard illusions of a possible military solution and to resume 
negotiations immediately and unconditionally. Russia will in 
every way promote precisely such a course. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

