<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Calls For Joint Efforts in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Calls For Joint Efforts in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105203894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1940 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105203894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn May 11 TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
said the leaders of the United Nations, the European Union, the 
United States, Germany, Russia, Britain, France and Yugoslav 
republics must join their efforts in search of ways to resolve 
the Bosnian crisis. 
  Speaking at a joint new conference after his talks with 
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in Bonn on Wednesday, Yeltsin said 
that for holding a meeting at such a level all parties must be 
absolutely sure that they will solve the problem. It will also 
require comprehensive preparatory work, he added. 
  The president said the foreign ministers have already held 
talks and begun working on the problem. 

</TEXT>

