<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, ROK President To Meet in Moscow in Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, ROK President To Meet in Moscow in Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105144294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1359 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Geronin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin will hold talks with South Korean President Kim Yong-sam 
during his visit to Moscow on June 1-4. 
  The two leaders will meet one-to-one and then hold talks in 
delegations. They will also have an informal meeting, Valentin 
Moyseyev, an Asia department official of the Russian Foreign 
Ministry's department, said on Wednesday. 
  Moyseyev said that during the visit the sides will sign a 
political document determining the main directions of future 
cooperation between Russia and South Korea. They are also 
expected to sign a package of agreements on various aspects of 
cooperation, including on environmental protection and 
prevention of incidents at sea and outside territorial waters of 
the two countries. 
  The Russian and South Korean foreign ministries have 
prepared 
and finalised a protocol on mutual exchanges. The sides may 
also sign an agreement on the protection of intellectual 
property. 
  Kim Yong-sam's visit will be his first trip to Russia, and 
the fifth Russian-South Korean summit meeting. 
  After Moscow, the South Korean leader will visit Tashkent 
for 
talks with Uzbek leaders on bilateral relations. 
  On the way back home, Kim Yong-sam plans to make a one-day 
stopover in Vladivostok to meet with local officials and discuss 
prospects for cooperation between South Korea and the Russian 
Far East. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

