<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on State Duma Budget Bill Debate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on State Duma Budget Bill Debate </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Chernomyrdin Calls for Balanced Budget </H4>

<F P=102> LD1105125794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1220 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- Chairman of the Russian 
Government, Viktor Chernomyrdin, believes that only a strictly 
balanced budget can mobilize the market. A statement to this 
effect was made by the Russian prime minister on Wednesday as he 
addressed lawmakers of the State Duma during debates on a draft 
law on the state budget for 1994. 
  According to Chernomyrdin, the suggested figures of 
budgetary 
expenditures and revenues and the budget deficit envisaged by 
the draft law and insisted upon by the Russian Government will 
enable to keep inflation rates under control. 
  If the suggested federal budget is not approved by the State 
Duma as soon as possible, the Government will be devoid of 
starting points necessary for the formation of its economic 
policy. If the Duma approves of key figures of the state 
budget, Russian lawmakers jointly with the Government will be 
able to finalize the draft in a calm and orderly way, 
redistribute funds and decide "where to channel extra funds and 
at whose expense," Chernomyrdin said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

