<H3> <TI>   Government Presidium Begins Examining Civil Defense Bill </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Presidium Begins Examining Civil Defense Bill </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205084394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0755 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 12 TASS -- A regular meeting of the 
Russian Government's Presidium, currently under way here, began 
with the examination of the bill "on civil defence". The 
meeting is chaired by Prime Minister Viktor Chenomyrdin. 
  After that the ministers will discuss the draft land code of 
Russia. Moreover, the Cabinet will hear reports on the drafts 
of two federal programmes -- to modernise the single system of 
air traffic in the Russian Federation for the period of up to 
2005 and on a target programme for 1994-1997 to protect Russian 
territories from the penetration and spreading of infectious 
diseases, which are particularly dangerous for human beings, 
animals and plants, and also of toxic substances. 

</TEXT>

