<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Taganrog Metallurgical Plant Halted"] </F>
  [Text] The Taganrog Metallurgical Plant, the largest 
enterprise in southern Russia, closed on Tuesday. It 
specialized in the production of pipes, mainly for the oil 
industry. 
  The main reason for the closure is that consumers owe the 
plant more than 20 billion rubles for output. The Taganrog 
plant does not have the means to pay for fuel for the 
open-hearth furnaces. 

</TEXT>

