<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern Border District To Be Set Up in Murmansk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern Border District To Be Set Up in Murmansk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105205294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1843 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the near future a Northern border district will 
be set up in Murmansk. It will include the territories from the 
Murmansk region to Chukotka, Governor of the Murmansk region 
Yevgeniy Komarov said at a conference in Murmansk dedicated to 
protection of Russia's northern borders. 
  He said that the border service in the Arctic region is 
being 
restructured, taking into account the development of large-scale 
ties between the Russian Federation, Norway and Finland, and the 
opening of the Northern sea route for passage of foreign vessels 
with stops in Russian ports. Besides, the need for the Northern 
border district is dictated by the increased interest of NATO in 
Russia's northern borders. 

</TEXT>

