<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Large-Scale Operation in Far East to Check Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Large-Scale Operation in Far East to Check Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105085094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0811 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Grachev] </F>
  [Text] Vladivostok May 11 TASS -- A large-scale operation, 
code-named "Foreigner", was launched on the entire maritime 
territory of the Russian Far East, beginning from 00 hours 
today. It is being carried out by Interior Ministry forces with 
the help of procurators, customs officials, and other services. 
  The main purpose of the operation is to check the observance 
of Russian residence laws and regulations by foreigners. 
  It is an open secret that the territory is now overrun by 
guests from CIS countries and other foreign states. What is 
more, their numbers can hardly be properly recorded. Many of 
them come to Russia legally, but then settle here arbitrarily, 
engaging in poaching, shady businesses, and other not very 
seemly occupations. Many come to the territory illegally, with 
forged documents, while some even have no documents at all. 
  Particularly many foreigners have settled in the Ussuri 
Taiga, which they are devastating most ruthlessly and 
impudently. Officials of the territorial interior department 
hope the operation "Foreigner", expected to last until May 20, 
will help the foreign guests to "learn the particulars" of the 
regulations in force and to respect Russia's laws. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-62057 </DOCNO>
