<H3> <TI>   Russian Partnership Variant Not Yet Considered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Partnership Variant Not Yet Considered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105144594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1347 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine's Defense Ministry has so far given no 
consideration to Russia's program alternative to NATO's 
Partnership for Peace scheme, Ukrainian Defense Minister Vitaly 
Radetsky said. 
  "We are still working out our vision" of the North Atlantic 
alliance's scheme, whose implementation poses "many problems" 
for Ukraine, Radetsky told Interfax-Ukraine on Wednesday. One 
of the problems is that Ukraine's military doctrine prevents it 
from joining any blocs, he said. 

</TEXT>

