<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Relations With Duma `Constructive' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Relations With Duma `Constructive' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205103594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0947 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 12 TASS -- "Constructive relations are 
shaping up between the Russian Government and the State Duma. 
This is very important for the Cabinet of Ministers," Russian 
Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin said during the opening of today's 
meeting of the Russian Government's Presidium, assessing the 
Duma's approval of the 1944 federal budget in first reading. 
  "We met with the Duma's understanding and I believe this was 
due to our common realisation that the fate of the country was 
being decided," Chernomyrdin stressed. "We shall base the joint 
budgetary work of ministers and lawmakers on methods of 
conviction," he added. According to Chernomyrdin, the Duma's 
preliminary approval of the budget laid the beginning for 
"concrete, painstaking work, in which the government will 
persistently uphold its viewpoint after taking into account 
everything that it had missed or overlooked". 
  The head of the Russian Government said that the budget 
financing of the defence complex was a most important problem. 
"Be what it may, we shall back the military-industrial complex 
and this refers to all its ministries and departments, including 
the Russian military science. As to the defence order, it is 
necessary to balance it out, after seeing what we have on hand 
this year and without exaggerating or hushing up problems," 
Chernomyrdin noted. 

</TEXT>

