<F P=102>   MK1205075094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 12 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1205075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Yuliya Kantor report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Borovoy </F>
Wants To Be President"] 
  [Text] "My name will emerge in the lists of candidates for 
the presidency in the upcoming elections because a refusal to 
contest them would be immoral," Konstantin Borovoy, leader of 
the Economic Freedom Party [EFP], who arrived in St. Petersburg 
yesterday, said in a meeting with journalists. The centerpiece 
of the visit will be talks about the implementation of the EFP's 
project to lift out of the crisis the country's air space 
industry, whose main centers are located, in particular, in St. 
Petersburg and in northwestern Russia. Regarding the situation 
in the country, Konstantin Borovoy described the just signed 
agreement on public accord as "the most cynical action 
conceivable." The EFP leader, who thinks that currently the 
Russian Government is pursuing an anti-market policy, said in 
that respect that he would "not join the Chernomyrdin 
government" under any circumstances. 

</TEXT>

