<H3> <TI>   Rutskoy Not Invited to Leaderhip Forum in Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rutskoy Not Invited to Leaderhip Forum in Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105142494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1348 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent yekaterina zhilyakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- Former Russian Vice-President 
Aleksandr Rutskoy was excluded from the list of people invited 
to the international week of cooperation of future leaders that 
opened in Moscow today, following his call for changes in the 
existing system in Russia made at a V-Day rally on May 9. 
  In an exclusive interview with ITAR-TASS on Wednesday, 
Aleksey Koshmarov, chairman of the Russian movement "Future 
Leaders of the New Millennium," said that about 200 young 
parliamentarians and members of various parties from Russia, the 
United States, France, Germany and other countries will try to 
shape up a new image of the political leader for the 21st 
century. 
  "A new type of politics must be distinctive in its 
unpredictability, ability to conduct a dialogue and seek a 
compromise, rather than conflicts," Koshmarov said. 
  He stressed that the members of the movement have been 
trying 
to avoid extremism, both right and left, since it was set up two 
years ago. 

</TEXT>

