<H3> <TI>   Police General Faces Criminal Arms Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police General Faces Criminal Arms Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105112394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1045 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Larisa Kislinskaya] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- Criminal charges were brought 
against Police Major-General Igor Shilov, first deputy head of 
the main criminal department of the Russian Interior Ministry. 
He is accused of illegal possession of arms, reliable sources 
told TASS on Wednesday. 
  Shilov was traced by the Moscow Department for Organised 
Crime when it arrested a certain Korneyev, a swindler with a big 
criminal record. 
  According to the sources, Shilov and his son maintained 
"corrupted links with Korneyev". 
  Investigators reportedly possess information that Shilov 
received bribes from the swindler, however head of the Moscow 
Department for Organised Crime Colonel Vladimir Rushaylo refused 
to provide any comment. 
  Shilov's son, who is an advanced student of the Police 
Academy, also faces criminal charges for illegal possession of 
weapons. 
  The case is being investigated by the Moscow prosecutor's 
office which said that a total of eight policemen are involved 
in it. Only one of them has been arrested. 
  Despite criminal charges Shilov still keeps his post. His 
and his son's apartments have been searched. The investigation 
is going on. 
  According to the "MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS" newspaper, a 
combat 
rifle with a sight and a big number of submachine-gun cartridges 
were discovered in Shilov's apartment. A big amount of 
ammunition was also found in his son's flat. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-62078 </DOCNO>
