<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Radio Longwave Transmissions To Cease </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Radio Longwave Transmissions To Cease </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105084494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1400 today, the Ministry of Communications 
reports, the transmitter relaying Russia's radio on 261 kH on 
the longwave will be switched off. This has been caused by an 
unpaid electricity bill. It is not for the first time that the 
problem of payments has emerged. It is not the company's debt 
which is at issue; the funds have not been provided from the 
state budget. The Government is intending to consider, in the 
nearest future, the problem of state radio and television -- 
specifically volumes of broadcasting and necessary funding. 
  We do regret, on our part, that our listeners will be unable 
to listen to Russia's Radio on its usual frequency, due to the 
fact that these problems are as yet unresolved. 

</TEXT>

