<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Rises by 250,000 This Year </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unemployment Rises by 250,000 This Year </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105111294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1051 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By BUSINESS-TASS correspondent Oleg Deyneko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- The number of officially 
registered unemployed has gone up in Russia by 250,000 people 
since the beginning of the year, BUSINESS-TASS learned from the 
Russian Economics Ministry on Wednesday. 
  A total of 1.4 million jobless people have applied for help 
at the employment service. 1.1 million of them were registered 
as unemployed and 80 per cent of them receive the dole. 
  The number of people who have been unemployed for more than 
four months running comprises 56 per cent of the total, 
according to the ministry. The figure was 42 per cent in the 
first quarter of 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

