<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Pay $4.7 Billion in Foreign Debts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Pay $4.7 Billion in Foreign Debts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105173494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1541 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- The Russian Government said 
Russia will pay 4.7 billion U.S. dollars as part of its foreign 
debt payments in 1994. 
  The State Duma adopted a law on Wednesday allowing the 
government to borrow as much in order to keep the balance and 
grant not more than 400 million dollars in credits to other 
countries. 
  Aleksandr Zhukov, one of the authors of the law, said this 
will be enough to finish facilities in foreign countries, the 
construction of which has been suspended. 

</TEXT>

