<H3> <TI>   Military Court Confirms Terekhov Dismissal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Court Confirms Terekhov Dismissal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105175294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1646 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 11 TASS -- Moscow's Military Court 
confirmed on Wednesday that the dismissal of Colonel Stanislav 
Terekhov from the army was legal. 
  Terekhov was sacked on September 23, 1993 by Russian Defence 
Minister Pavel Grachev for violation of the contract and 
disobeying his commanders, ITAR-TASS learnt from sources close 
to the Defence Ministry. 
  Terekhov, who is also chairman of the Union of Army 
Officers, 
was detained on charges of plotting an attack on the 
headquarters of CIS united armed forces after President Boris 
Yeltsin dissolved the parliament last autumn and has been in 
custody since then. 
  Terekhov did not deny the charges, but said he was against 
using guns. He was released under amnesty earlier this year. 
  Additionally, Terekhov is charged with participation in May 
Day riots in 1993 which killed one and injured dozens of people. 

</TEXT>

