<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Inspection Carried Out"] </F>
  [Text] On 2 May, the Government of Finland turned to the 
Government of the Russian Federation with a request, in line 
with the provision of the Vienna 1992 document on 
confidence-building measures and security, to carry out an 
inspection on the territory of Leningrad Military District in 
the area of Alakurtti, Plyarnyye Zori, Primorskiy, and Selkyalya. 
  The Russian Federation Defense Ministry Information and 
Press 
Directorate reports that the Finnish side's request has been 
met. On 4 May, a Finnish inspection group comprising four 
representatives of Finland's Armed Forces arrived in the 
designated area where it conducted an inspection over 48 hours. 

