<H3> <TI>   Severodvinsk Nuclear Submarine Construction Delayed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Severodvinsk Nuclear Submarine Construction Delayed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1105154094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 11 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK1105154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Own correspondent Vladimir Gundarov report from </F>
Severodvinsk under the "In Brief" rubric: "At Present, Ships 
Are Also Born in Pain"] 
  [Text] The creation of the "Severodvinsk" nuclear-powered 
submarine -- KRASNAYA ZVEZDA reported the laying of its keel in 
late December -- has entailed painstaking efforts from the first 
days of building work. The shipbuilders are not satisfied with 
the quality of design documents, which, according to 
specialists, can bear no criticism. This is not the sole reason 
for wrecking the timetable of work on the building stocks, 
however. According to M. Zhukov, who is responsible for 
commissioning the ship, the main reason are undersupplies of 
metal and steel work because "Sevmashpredpriyatiye" 
[Severodvinsk Engineering Enterprise] does not have money to pay 
to supplier plants in advance. 

</TEXT>

