<H3> <TI>   Smolensk AES Signs Cooperation Accord With Belarus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Smolensk AES Signs Cooperation Accord With Belarus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1105151094 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 11 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1105151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Viktor Artemenko report from Smolensk: "Smolensk `Electric </F>
Bulb' in Belarus Homes"] 
  [Text] It is a pleasant and rare occasion considering the 
days we live in -- a five-year treaty of cooperation between the 
Smolensk AES [Atomic Electric Power Station) and the Belorussian 
[Belarus] Energy Ministry has been signed. 
  The document envisions mutually advantageous terms of 
technical and material assistance, and the provision of 
scientific and technical information. 
  This event was preceded by another, no less important event 
-- a 750-kilovolt power transmission line originating at the 
"Belorusskaya" substation at the Smolensk AES was put in 
operation. 
  The 750-kilovolt power transmission line was constructed 
jointly by builders and operation personnel of Smolensk's 
Desnogorsk and of Belorussia. A large group of builders and 
operation personnel of the Smolensk AES were awarded 
certificates of honor of Belorussia's Supreme Soviet and the 
Ministry of Power Engineering for this successful work. 

</TEXT>

