<H3> <TI>   Defense Industry Trade Union Plans Protest Action </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Industry Trade Union Plans Protest Action </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1205073094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 12 May 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK1205073094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [RIA report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- On 9 June, enterprises of the Russian 
defense complex will halt the output of civilian products and 
consumer goods for five to ten minutes, and will accompany this 
action by blowing their sirens. A decision to this effect has 
been made by the Central Council of the sectoral trade union in 
support of the initiative of "defense workers" of Novosibirsk, 
Vladimir, Kirov, Moscow, and a number of other oblasts. "We 
hope to impress the government, which continues to ignore the 
needs of the sector's working people," said the union leader 
Sergey Shuklin. Simultaneously, he intimated, it was suggested 
that work collectives discuss at the rallies, meetings, and 
conferences whether it is wise to go over to the extreme form of 
protest -- a strike. In Shuklin's words, military-industrial 
complex working people "do not demand any subsidies or 
privileges, and only insist on the most essential thing -- to be 
paid on time and to keep their jobs." 

</TEXT>

