<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aide Confirms Armenian, Azerbaijani Presidents To Meet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aide Confirms Armenian, Azerbaijani Presidents To Meet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105152394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1347 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In his interview with Interfax Levon Zubaryan, aide 
of the Armenian president, reconfirmed the information about the 
preparation for a meeting between Armenian and Azerbaijani 
presidents on the settlement of the Karabakh conflict scheduled 
for the near term in Moscow. At the same time he reported that 
the precise date is as yet unknown. According to Zubaryan, 
"preparatory diplomatic work is being carried out with the 
mediation of the Russian side." 
  In Zubaryan's words, this meeting has been foreseen by the 
protocol signed on the results of the meeting between 
representatives of the parliaments of Armenia, Azerbaijan, and 
Nagorno-Karabakh under the mediation of the CIS 
Inter-Parliamentary Assembly on May 5 in Bishkek. 
  One of the items of the protocol says that the appeals to 
cease fire in the conflict zone should be fixed "in the near 
term by signing a reliable and legal agreement which would 
stipulate a mechanism preventing resumption of any military and 
hostile actions, withdrawal of forces from the occupied 
territories, restoration of communications, return of refugees, 
and continuation of the negotiation process." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

