<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Halts Call-up Due To Lack of Funds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Halts Call-up Due To Lack of Funds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205101794 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 0900 GMT 12 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Latvian army has not conscripted soldiers for 
compulsory service since the end of April. The call-up was 
suspended due to lack of funds in the budget needed to maintain 
and train soldiers. Aleksandrs Doniks, head of the state 
service department, told the LABRIT newspaper that the call-up 
has been suspended until the number of soldiers on compulsory 
service falls and there is enough money to maintain them. 
  According to estimates made by the Defense Ministry at the 
beginning of this year, the maintenance of a soldier for the 
duration of his service costs approximately 1,050 lats, 
excluding the funds needed to buy machinery, arms, and 
ammunition. If the call-up is suspended for a longer time, then 
toward the fall there will be a shortage of about 750 soldiers 
on the border. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

