<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kohl Begin Closed Session Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kohl Begin Closed Session Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105134494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1322 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By special ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Bonn, 11 May -- Russia's President Boris Yeltsin and 
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl have begun their talks at the FRG 
chancellor's department in Bonn. The talks are being held 
behind closed doors. They will subsequently be continued with 
other delegation members taking part. 
  It is thought that the issue of finalizing the withdrawal of 
Russian troops will be one of the main topics on the agenda of 
the consultatons between B. Yeltsin and H. Kohl. Considerable 
attention will also be focused on the problems of economic 
cooperation between the FRG and Russia, and topical 
international political problems. 
  B. Yeltsin and H. Kohl will today hold a joint news 
conference on the results of the talks in Bonn. 

</TEXT>

