<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Russian leadership continues a policy of 
blockade and isolation against the Chechen republic, a statement 
of the Chechen Foreign Ministry transferred to Interfax on 
Wednesday says. 
  "For us the fact of forming a delegation led by Vice-Premier 
Sergey Shakhray for talks with the Chechen republic by 
resolution of the Russian government dated May 3 is just another 
step of such a policy," the statement says. 
  "However in reality this delegation of the Russian 
Federation 
turned out to be formed for talks with the leadership of the 
Chechen opposition who have already arrived in Moscow," the 
Chechen Foreign Ministry notes. "The will of the Chechen people 
and efforts of its legitimate president aimed at the settlement 
of relations with the Russian Federation are ignored once again." 
  The Chechen Foreign ministry urged all international 
organizations and the press "to condemn actions by the Russian 
leadership running contrary to the norms and principles of 
international law." 

</TEXT>

