<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belarus Proposes Division of Former USSR Ships </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belarus Proposes Division of Former USSR Ships </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205162894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belarus intends to propose considering the division 
of non-military ships of the former USSR's fleet at a CIS 
summit. As Interfax learned in the press service of the CIS 
Executive Secretariat, at the initiative of the Belarussian side 
a meeting of CIS experts is scheduled for next week to discuss 
this issue. 
  In the meantime, a high-ranking official of the Belarussian 
Foreign Ministry, who requested anonymity, told Interfax "this 
idea most probably will be once again killed, because the states 
who are currently owners of non-military ships of the former 
USSR are unlikely to allow this issue to be put on the agenda of 
a CIS summit." 
  The source believes that a significant number of former 
Soviet non-military ships have already been privatized or 
mothballed for a long term. In his opinion, "the time to 
achieve the fleet's division may have been irreversibly missed." 

</TEXT>

