<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kurils To Get R85 Billion in Federal Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kurils To Get R85 Billion in Federal Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1305105594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 12 May 94 p II </F>
<F P=103> PM1305105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ADS report under the "Regional News" rubric: "Government </F>
Is Allocating 85 Billion Rubles to South Kurils" -- from the 
FINANSOVYYE IZVESTIYA section] 
  [Text] Sakhalin Oblast Administration has received 
notification from the Economy Ministry regarding the allocation 
of 85 billion rubles [R] in 1994 to the federal program titled 
"The Social and Economic Development of the Kuril Islands for 
1994, 1995, and Through 2000." Sakhalin Oblast Vice Governor 
Viktor Serenko announced that R26.6 billion of this sum would be 
channeled into modernizing or constructing airports and seaports 
on Iturup and Kunashir, and also developing the power industry 
and air transportation and communications. In addition, R24.89 
billion will be allocated in the form of investment loans to 
enterprises that take part in implementing these projects. The 
remaining R34.45 billion are earmarked for current expenditure 
(transportation costs and freight and food deliveries). 

</TEXT>

