<H4>    Kinkel Urges Help on European Integration </H4>

<F P=102> LD1305100794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0929 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1305100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents] </F>
  [Text] Bonn May 13 TASS -- German Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel told the Russian president on Friday that Germany is 
ready to promote Russian integration into European organisations. 
  "We have stated our readiness to help Russia in its joining 
all European structures which are important for it at present -- 
the Council of Europe, GATT. We also intend to support your 
country in joining the trade regime, which will be set up after 
the elimination of Cocom [Coordinating Committee for 
Multilateral Export Control], and surely, (in joining) the 
`Partnership for Peace'", he told reporters describing his talk 
with Boris Yeltsin. 
  The problem of mutual restitution of cultural valuables 
seized during the Second World War was also raised. "We 
understand the delicacy with which the Russian side treats the 
issue. But I once again drew the attention of the president to 
the great importance of the problem for us", Kinkel told TASS. 

</TEXT>

