<H3> <TI>   Continued Reportage on Yeltsin's Visit to Germany </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continued Reportage on Yeltsin's Visit to Germany </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Yeltsin Not Returning Gutenberg Bible </H4>

<F P=102> MK1305091094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 13 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1305091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA unheadlined report under the "Visit" </F>
rubric] 
  [Text] Responding to a question from a NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA 
correspondent, Russian Federation Culture Minister Mikhail 
Shvydkoy stated that "according to Culture Ministry 
information," the Russian president had set off for talks with 
Chancellor Kohl bringing along none of the books and other 
valuable objects in the so-called restitution category, or in 
other words, those taken to the USSR from the territory of 
Germany during the war and during the early post-war years. 
Hence the rumors about Boris Yeltsin's making a gift to the 
German side of the world-famous rarity -- the Gutenberg Bible -- 
are just rumors. But, alternative sources report, books from 
the Gotha Library may still be delivered to Germany toward the 
visit's end. 

</TEXT>

