<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Committee Head Questions Joint Exercise With U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Committee Head Questions Joint Exercise With U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305122694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1101 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1305122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Artyushin] </F>
  [Text] Bryansk May 13 TASS -- "Russia cannot be made a 
training ground for the American Army," Russian Federation 
Security and Defence Committee Chairman Pyotr Shirshov said in 
an interview with ITAR-TASS. 
  Commenting on forthcoming joint Russian-American exercises 
to 
be organized on the Totsk training ground in the Orenburg 
region, Shirshov said that for organizing such an arrangement at 
first a legal procedure must be devised. "We do not have any 
laws, in compliance with which foreign troops could be invited 
to Russia," deputy to the Federal Assembly from Bryansk said. 
  Regarding the possiblity of Russia's participation in NATO's 
"Partnership for Peace" programme, Pyotr Shirshov called it a 
"danger for Russia". In his opinion, by participating in this 
programme Russia does not gain anything from the point of view 
of any access to NATO strategies and workings, and 
simultaneously, the Russian Army "becomes transparent to the 
North Atlantic bloc." 

</TEXT>

