<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protesters Demand Cancellation of Joint U.S. Exercise </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protesters Demand Cancellation of Joint U.S. Exercise </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1305114994 Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN in Russian 13 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1305114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Ivan Gavrilenko report: "One `Desert Storm' Will Suffice"] </F>
  [Text] The Orenburg Oblast Administration building has 
been picketed. The participants in this protest action demanded 
the cancellation of Russian-U.S. exercises in the Totsk training 
area and the rejection of cooperation with servicemen from the 
U.S. Third Infantry Division under the command of General 
Holder, which participated in operation "Desert Storm" in Iraq. 
  Earlier, local representatives of 14 public movements and 
parties, including the Orenburg organization of the Agrarian 
Party, protested the joint exercises in Totsk. 
  The protest against the "peacemaking exercises" is beginning 
to strike a chord in other oblasts and republics in the Urals 
and Volga region. 

</TEXT>

