<H3> <TI>   Russia Said Planning To Stop Gas Supplies to Georgia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Said Planning To Stop Gas Supplies to Georgia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205122894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia will not supply Georgian customers with 
natural gas in 1994. This is what knowledgeable sources in the 
Russian Gazprom organization told the (OIL INFORMATION AGENCY). 
  According to the Russian gas distribution plan approved for 
this year, Gazprom intends to have all surplus raw material 
resources sent to Ukraine to be stored in underground gas 
storage depots to ensure uninterrupted gas supplies to western 
European countries. 
  Georgia currently receives natural gas from Turkmenistan. 

</TEXT>

