<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin's Envoy Hails Moldovan-Dniester Rapprochement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin's Envoy Hails Moldovan-Dniester Rapprochement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205205194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2028 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205205194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correpondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 12 TASS -- The determination of Moldova 
and its breakaway Dniester region to improve their mutual 
relations is designed to subdue the entire conflict, the Russian 
president's special envoy for Moldova Vladillen Vasev said on 
Thursday in an interview with TASS, commenting on the joint 
statement signed by the Moldovan and Dniester leaders. 
  The document signed the other day is quite constructive and 
can lay down a good basis for further negotiations on the whole 
set of problems facing the confronting sides, Russia's envoy 
stressed. 
  "Both sides have come to understand that the situation 
developing in Moldova and its Dniester region calls for a 
pragmatic approach. As a result, the sides managed to find 
mutually acceptable variants of conflict settlement", he noted. 
  Vasev laid a special emphasis on the fact that the signed 
document stressed the need for defining the state and legal 
status of the Dniester region. "This is to considerably 
facilitate further efforts aiming to draw the conflicting sides 
closer together", he pointed out. 
  The sides also reached a compromise on a transition period 
and a gradual acquirement by the Dniester region of its state 
and legal status, the Russian diplomat reported. 
  There has recently been certain progress in relations 
between 
Moldova and its separatist province, which agreed upon 
approaches to solution of the most pressing problems. "However, 
I would warn against excessive optimism at the moment, since a 
lot of differences remain to be settled yet, including through 
Russia's mediation", Vasev stressed. 

</TEXT>

