<H3> <TI>   Gen Lebed Terms Dniester Leaders `Incompetent' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gen Lebed Terms Dniester Leaders `Incompetent' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205152694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1228 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] May 12 TASS -- Commander of the 
Russian 14th Army, deployed in the Moldovan break-away Dniester 
province, Aleksandr Lebed has accused the leadership of the 
self-proclaimed republic of attempts to blame Russian military 
for the worsening economic situation. 
  The general rejected accusations by Dniester Bank Chairman 
Vyacheslav Zagryadskiy, quoted by local media, that the field 
bank of the Russian Army allegedly bought 39 billion of Dniester 
roubles (interim currency made from old Soviet banknotes by 
sticking a special stamp with a portrait of Russian 
Field-Marshal Aleksandr Suvorov). The Army was buying Dniester 
roubles in order to undermine the economy, the banker claimed. 
  "There is not a single Dniester rouble in the money-box of 
the Army field bank", the general told ITAR-TASS today adding 
that the economic catastrophe of the region had been caused by 
its "incompetent and thieving leadership". 
  This is not the first time that Lebed accused Dniester 
leaders of financial embezzlements and corruption. 

</TEXT>

