<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Ready To Promote' Peace in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government `Ready To Promote' Peace in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205134094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1256 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 12 TASS -- Russia called on warring 
Yemeni leaders to stop fighting and said it is ready to promote 
an end to the conflict and help ensure peace in the country. 
  "The government of the Russian Federation again insistently 
calls on the warring sides to immediately cease fire and reach 
an agreement on armistice", the Russian Government said in a 
statement on Thursday. 
  "The Yemeni leaders should find strength to make the final 
choice towards a peaceful political settlement of 
contradictions. Moscow is sure that peaceful ways out of the 
Yemeni crisis do exist", according to the statement. 
  "Moscow believes that Yemeni leaders realise the 
inadmissibility and senselessness of the continuing bloodshed, 
the inevitable consequences of the fratricidal war for the 
future of the Yemeni people", it added. 
  "In the current critical situation it is especially 
important 
to be above emotions and settling accounts, to show state 
wisdom, abide by common sense and long-term interests of the 
country and its citizens", according to the document. 
  The government stressed that the tragic developments in 
Yemen 
cause great concern and reiterated that it is ready to actively 
promote efforts aimed at a peaceful settlement of the conflict, 
at restoring peace and quietness in the ancient country. 

</TEXT>

