<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK `Warned' To Observe Loggers' Human Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK `Warned' To Observe Loggers' Human Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205132894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1244 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Aleksandr Krylovich </F>
and Vladimir Taranov] 
  [Text] Moscow May 12 TASS -- Russia warned North Korea on 
Thursday that if the human rights of its lumberjacks in the 
Russian Far East are not observed, it will not prolong a 
corresponding agreement with Pyongyang. 
  Russian Foreign Ministry Spokesman Mikhail Demurin told a 
briefing that a Russian delegation is leaving soon for North 
Korea to discuss a new agreement on timber processing in 
Khabarovsk and Amur regions as the latest one expired in 1993. 
  "The Russian side believes that the most important article 
of 
the new document should become the provision, according to which 
the rights of citizens of the People's Democratic Republic of 
Korea working in Russia should correspond to Russian legislation 
and international norms", he said. 
  Russian press reports said that the rights of North Korean 
workers are being rudely violated by their authorities. 
  "If no agreement (on human rights) is reached Russia will 
consider itself free from the rights and obligations fixed in 
the earlier agreement", Demurin stressed. 
  He also informed that Russian-North Korean talks at the 
level 
of deputy foreign ministers began in Moscow on Thursday. "The 
sides plan to consider the whole complex of bilateral relations 
and international problems", according to Demurin. 
  He explained that this includes political and economic 
relations, key aspects of the situation on the Korean Peninsula, 
including the nuclear non-proliferation problems and the Russian 
proposal to convene an international conference on security and 
nuclear-free status of Korea. 

</TEXT>

