<F P=106> [NOYAN TAPAN report: "Vaan Avakyan Arrested"] </F>
  [Text] The arrest of the former first deputy chief adviser 
to the president of the country on national security, Vaan 
Avakyan, in a Moscow airport where he had arrived from Bulgaria 
was announced in Yerevan. Avakyan was in Sofia until recently. 
The arrested person was turned over to Yerevan. Vaan Avakyan 
stands accused of trying to take documents containing state 
secrets outside the country. The arrest was coordinated with 
the Procuracy of Russia and the Russian special services. The 
investigation is being conducted by the investigatory department 
of the State National Security Administration of the Republic of 
Armenia. It is assumed that on 9 May, Avakyan will be permitted 
to see a lawyer. 

</TEXT>

