  [Text] Baku, 12 May (AZERTAC)--The Azeri Armed Forces have 
been fighting for more than 24 hours, trying to restitute 
villages of Seysulan and Gapanli, which are situated in the 
district of Terterskiy and were occupied by the Armenian Armed 
Forces yesterday. According to the Defence Ministry of 
Azerbaijan, Azeri soldiers drove out the enemy from the village 
of Gapanli yesterday in the evening. The Armenian Armed Forces 
