<H3> <TI>   Yerevan Radio Reports Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yerevan Radio Reports Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1205210994 Yerevan Radio Yerevan in Azeri 1330 GMT 12 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1205210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dear listeners, we now present a report on the 
latest incidents in the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] and the 
border between Armenia and Azerbaijan. 
  The situation on NKR's front line continues to be unstable. 
Regardless of the protocol Azerbaijan signed in Bishkek, that 
Republic has violated the cease-fire by intensely firing on the 
Armenian defense positions with various types of arms. 
Furthermore, it has launched extensive attacks with armored 
vehicles every day. The situation in Mardakerskiy and Agdamskiy 
Rayons is tense. However, it must be stressed that the effort by 
the Azerbaijan Military Command Headquarters to take the 
initiative at the front line has not achieved its objective. As 
usual, the NKR defense forces have repulsed the enemy attacks 
and forced Azerbaijan's units to retreat after suffering 
casualties and losing military equipment. 
  A short while ago the NKR Defense Army Headquarters Press 
Service disclosed that Azerbaijan's military forces had attacked 
the NKR defense positions in Agdamskiy Rayon this morning. A 
wave of artillery shelling preceded their onslaught. However, 
they failed to achieve their goal. The NKR units rebuffed their 
attack and forced them to retreat after suffering casualties and 
losing military equipment. 
  According to the NKR intelligence units, Azerbaijan has 
begun 
to deploy additional military units in Mardakertskiy Rayon's 
northern areas. [passage indistinct] 
  An enemy infantry unit made up of 300 men attacked [place 
name indistinct], Yarymdzha, and [place name indistinct] in 
Mardakertskiy Rayon yesterday. Their attack was preceded by an 
intensive wave of artillery fire. Violent clashes took place in 
the region. The NKR forces not only blocked the attack, but 
also counterattacked. Initial reports from the area said the 
Azerbaijani units lost 60 men, while two men were killed and 11 
were wounded on the Armenian side. 
  Clashes occurred in the western side of [place name 
indistinct] in Agdamskiy Rayon yesterday afternoon. Meanwhile, 
the enemy shelled the NKR defense positions in the direction of 
the Omar Pass in the northern part of Fizulinskiy and 
Kelbadzharskiy Rayons with artillery. No one was hurt. The 
Armenians [words indistinct] return the fire. The military 
operations continued throughout the day. The NKR military units 
launched counterattacks. They completely liberated [place name 
indistinct] in Mardakertskiy Rayon. 
  In short, [words indistinct]. But no noticeable change has 
occurred in the operations zone. 
  The situation on the border between Armenia and Azerbaijan 
has been relatively peaceful during the past few days. 

</TEXT>

