<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visits National Security Council, State Department </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visits National Security Council, State Department </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1305105294 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0500 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1305105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Ukrainian delegation consisting of Ukrainian 
Deputy Prime Minister Valeriy Shmarov, Foreign Deputy Minister 
Borys Tarasyuk, and Volodymyr Horbulin, director of Ukraine's 
National Space Agency, has begun a working visit in Washington. 
The delegation members visited the U.S. National Security 
Council where they held consultations with Senior Director 
Nicholas Burns and Anthony Lake, national security adviser to 
the U.S. President. Major emphasis was put on issues related to 
the implementation of conversion projects for the Ukrainian 
defense industry and continued Ukrainian-U.S. cooperation in the 
sphere of nuclear equipment and technology. The delegation also 
held consultations at the U.S. State Department, where it 
discussed the implementation of trilateral agreements between 
Ukraine, Russia, and the United States, as well as other 
Ukrainian-U.S. agreements. Steps were outlined to hasten this 
process. 

</TEXT>

