<H3> <TI>   Joint Black Sea Fleet Exercises To Be Held in Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Black Sea Fleet Exercises To Be Held in Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205174294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The naval exercises Breeze-94 in the Black Sea due 
between 25 and 29 July were in the center of attention of the 
Wednesday meeting in Odessa between the chief of staff of the 
Bulgarian Navy Admiral Ilia Popov and the Deputy Commander of 
the Ukrainian Navy Rear-Admiral Nikolay Kostrov. According to 
INTERFAX-Ukraine, the details of interaction of the two navies 
were discussed. The exercises are going to involve two 
Ukrainian, one Russian and one Turkish ships, two missile 
cruisers from Greece and Rumania each as well as two ships of 
the U.S. sixth fleet. Two Bulgarian naval ships, a frigate and 
a demagnetizing vessel, are now visiting Odessa. On Saturday 
they are going to leave for Novorossiisk. 

</TEXT>

