<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Spokesman Criticizes Rutskoy 9 May Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Spokesman Criticizes Rutskoy 9 May Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205175694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The spokesman for the chairman of the State Duma, 
Dmitriy Biryukov, has said that the appeal by Former Vice 
President Aleksandr Rutskoy, made at the opposition rally at 
Lubyanka Square on May 9, in which he promised to mark the 50th 
anniversary of the victory over fascist Germany by "victory over 
the present regime", does not correspond to the "sentiments of 
millions of Russians who celebrated the May 9th holiday as a day 
of national accord". This is said in the Biryukov's statement 
sent to the media. 
  The spokesman is sure that under the difficult social and 
political situation in the country, "one cannot but recollect 
the promises given by those who were amnestied by the decision 
of the State Duma [no closing quotation mark as received]. 
  He said that some statements made on Victory Day "indicate 
that some people forgot their promises." 
  Biryukov said that the amnesty was not an unconditional 
action permitting further statements and actions. 
  He believes that public statements which could lead to a 
violation of the balance in relations between the authorities 
and the country's groupings should attract the attention of the 
Russian Prosecutor's Office. 

</TEXT>

