<H3> <TI>   Shakhray Rumored To Lose Ministerial Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shakhray Rumored To Lose Ministerial Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1305081094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 13 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1305081094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [SEGODNYA report: "Sergey Shakhray To Be Deprived of </F>
Ministerial Portfolio"] 
  [Text] SEGODNYA has learned from reliable sources that 
even before his visit to the FRG began, Boris Yeltsin signed an 
edict on relieving Sergey Shakhray of his post of minister for 
the affairs of nationalities and regional policy. He will be 
replaced be Nikolay Yegorov, who is currently administration 
chief of Krasnoyarsk Kray. Mr. Shakhray will retain the post of 
deputy prime minister, however. All his deputy ministers -- 
particularly, Messrs. Kotenkov and Abdulatipov -- have also been 
fired. 
  Observers infer that Sergey Shakhray's removal may have been 
prompted by the increasing clout of the Federation components' 
political elites following local elections. In addition, Sergey 
Shakhray's successful efforts to obtain funds to implement 
programs for the North could not but encounter stiff resistance 
on the part of southern Russia's lobby. 

</TEXT>

