<H3> <TI>   Rumors Reportedly Well-Founded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rumors Reportedly Well-Founded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305074394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 13 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305074394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In is believed in the presidential administration 
that rumours about Sergey Shakhray's dismissal from his 
ministerial post are to some extent well-founded. A 
presidential administration official who asked not to be 
identified explained the emerging reports by the fact that the 
Russian Government had recently decided, with Sergey Shakhray's 
active contribution, to finance three programs for the north, 
which had seriously affected the financial interests of the 
south of Russia. Another important factor was the unsuccessful 
policy toward the Cossacks and Chechnya. In particular, no one 
had authorized him to conduct talks with the Chechen opposition. 

</TEXT>

