<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 13 TASS -- The press service of the 
Russian Government confirmed that Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin had a 20-minute meeting with nationalist leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy on Thursday, but refused to give any 
comments. 
  "Government services refrain from any comments on the matter 
so far", a spokesman of the press service told TASS. "One can 
judge about the essence of the talk only from what the LDPR 
leader said", he added. 
  Zhirinovskiy told reporters after the meeting with 
Chernomyrdin that he had proposed to the prime minister to 
replace some of the ministers with members of his "shadow 
cabinet". 
  Zhirinovskiy is mostly against Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev and Privatization Minister Anatoliy Chubays. 

</TEXT>

