<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   LDP Seeks Ministerial Posts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    LDP Seeks Ministerial Posts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205183394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1614 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] LDP [Liberal Democratic Party] leader Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy has ended a meeting with Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin by raising the question of the party's involvement 
in government management. 
  In an interview with Interfax, Zhirinovskiy spoke of 
offering 
three possible options to the Prime Minister. Under the first 
option, the LDP wants three ministerial posts in the so-called 
power structures -- defence, police and counter-intelligence. 
  If not, the party is ready to settle for the posts of 
justice 
minister and prosecutor general. 
  The final option provides for the posts of economics 
minister 
and chairman of the state property committee. 
  Zhirinovskiy said the prime minister would now contemplate 
the proposals while "we will also think of what position to take 
towards the government in future". 

</TEXT>

