<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Congratulates TV, Radio Workers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Congratulates TV, Radio Workers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205111494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0837 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 12 May -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
has congratulated the workforce of the All Russian Television 
and Radio Company on the occasion of its third anniversary, 
which is marked today. 
  "I well remember the first broadcasts of Russian radio and 
Russian television," the Russian leader commented. "These 
events were a true festival of democracy and glasnost, the 
enthusiasm of journalists, and the sincere desire to tell and 
show the truth. 
  "Not everything worked out or is working out. There are not 
a few problems, faced with which, I know, one sometimes loses 
heart. But stand firm and I am sure that you will succeed 
honorably in travelling the difficult path of our Russian 
reforms. 
  "I will never forget that many-hours-long broadcast of that 
awful October night [Russian TV's special all-night program 
during the conflict with the Supreme Soviet in October 1993], 
which has become a masterpiece of television. I bow before your 
courage and loyalty to your professional duty. I believe in the 
enormous creative potential of your workforce. I wish you new 
successes," the president of Russia stressed. 

</TEXT>

