<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kokoshin on Development of Weapons System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kokoshin on Development of Weapons System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1305075094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 13 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1305075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "In the Interests of Developing </F>
Promising Technologies"] 
  [Text] The first sitting of the presidium of the Russian 
Academy of Rocket and Artillery Sciences (RARAS), recently 
reinstated by a Russian Federation presidential edict, has taken 
place in Moscow. Taking part in the sitting was Andrey 
Kokoshin, Russian Federation first deputy defense minister. 
  The Russian Academy of Rocket and Artillery Sciences, he 
underlined in his address, is supposed to be an important body 
bringing together leading scholars in various fields. Its main 
task is to develop promising technologies for weapons systems 
using artillery and rocket arms. Among these are a series of 
baseline military technologies that occupy an intermediate 
position, as it were, between basic research and applied 
development. 
  In the words of the first deputy defense minister, among the 
Russian military technology priorities is the creation of 
intelligent weapon systems capable of striking primarily the 
"nerve centers" of the opposing side's armed forces, and putting 
out of commission the enemy's combat equipment. 
  Despite the enormous difficulties of financing the defense 
needs, the Defense Ministry is doing all it can to ensure 
progress in these priorities. And here we have, in the past two 
years, a whole range of world-level achievements, Colonel 
General Anatoliy Sitnov, chief of armaments of the Russian 
Federation Armed Forces, pointed out in his address. 
  The RARAS presidium also discussed a range of specific areas 
of scientific research and development in line with the 
decisions made by the Russian Defense Ministry Council on 
Military-Technical Policy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

