<H3> <TI>   Chornovil Announces Changes in Parliamentary Regulations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chornovil Announces Changes in Parliamentary Regulations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205182694 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1300 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcement by Vyacheslav Chornovil, member of the </F>
presidium of the Ukrainian Supreme Council, chairing a session 
of the Supreme Council in Kiev -- live] 
  [Text] In connection with examining the credentials 
commission's submission [concerning the powers of seven 
parliamentary deputies] a certain change has taken place in 
respect of the validity of decisions being made by us. As a 
result, the Supreme Council is legally qualified to pass a 
decision, if 224 deputies are present at the session, rather 
than 226 as was the case previously. Then ...[pauses] but more 
than half its constitutional list, which is 226. [sentence as 
heard] 
  A decision is now passed by a majority of 169 out of the 
number of people's deputies whose powers are recognized. It was 
170 earlier. As for amendments to the Constitution, there 
remains the same norm as before, which is 300. 
  Decisions on the inclusion of issues on the agenda are 
passed 
by a majority of one third of the number of people's deputies, 
which now is 112. So these norms have been slightly reduced. 

</TEXT>

