<H3> <TI>   Radiation Levels Rise After `Very Serious' Cesium Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radiation Levels Rise After `Very Serious' Cesium Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205162294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A capsule containing Cesium-137, a highly 
radioactive substance, was stolen from the incineration workshop 
of a facility in the Ukrainian city of Nikolayev about two days 
ago, a correspondent for INTERFAX-Ukraine reports. Police have 
so far failed to track down either the culprits or the capsule 
which is believed to have been sawn up. 
  Spokesman for the Ukrainian security services Anatoliy 
Sakhno 
described the incident as very serious indeed. 
  Three of the plant employees have been sent for medical 
treatment in Kharkov and Kiev following symptoms of exposure to 
excessive radiation and about ten others are examined locally. 
  Unconfirmed reports speak of background radiation levels on 
the plant's premises rising. It is believed that parts of the 
capsule may have been thrown in the plant's water reservoir. 

</TEXT>

