BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 12 May TASS -- The Ukrainian Government has 
issued a resolution on measures aimed to stabilize energy 
supplies to the national economy. 
  According to the resolution, new generating units will be 
put 
into action at several nuclear power plants at the nearest 
future and new power transmission lines will be constructed to 
deliver the electric power. 
  The Ukrainian State Committee for Use of Nuclear Power and 
Ministry for Power Engineering and Electrification are 
instructed to modify existing tariffs for electric energy at an 
early date. 
  Relevant organizations are instructed to report on available 
opportunities and terms for increasing generating capacities of 
the active nuclear power plants and to map out a programme for 
developing nuclear power engineering and industry in Ukraine. 

