<H3> <TI>   Socioeconomic, Oil, Gas Development Plans Discussed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socioeconomic, Oil, Gas Development Plans Discussed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205202794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2016 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 13 May TASS -- A plan for socio-economic 
development of Ukraine in 1995 aims primarily at overcoming 
inflation, stabilizing economic output, and raising the people's 
living standards. 
  The plan was considered on Thursday [12 May] at a session of 
the collegium of the Ukrainian Economics Ministry. It also 
highlights demonopolizing national economy; fostering small 
businesses; forming stock market and implementing agricultural 
reform. 
  The participants in the session also discussed a national 
programme called "Ukraine's oil and gas -- 2010", which provided 
for a comprehensive evaluation of opportunities to increase both 
national oil and gas production and reserves. 
  At present, Ukraine's own gas and oil production may meet 9 
to 11 percent (4 mln tonnes) of its oil consumption needs and 18 
to 20 percent (18 bln cubic meters) of its gas consumption needs. 
  An effective use of its natural resources may enable Ukraine 
to stabilize and, in the long run, increase its oil and gas 
production to a measure. 

</TEXT>

