<H3> <TI>   Snegur Against Russian Military Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur Against Russian Military Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205210994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1934 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kishinyov [Chisinau] does not agree that the 
withdrawal of the Fourteenth Russian Army from Moldova be 
synchronized with granting a special juridical status to 
Transdniestria. This was stated by Moldovan President Mircea 
Snegur at his meeting with Deputy U.S. State Secretary, Chief 
Coordinator on the New Independent States James Collins in 
Kishinyov today. Snegur said the issue was being discussed with 
Russia. 
  Snegur stressed that no Russian military base could be 
established on Moldovan territory. Information on its 
establishment was not more than an allegation by the media, he 
added. 
  James Collins stated that the participation of Moldova in 
international organizations and its signing of the NATO 
Partnership for Peace program proved once again that the 
Republic was moving towards democratization of its society. He 
highly appraised the general vision of possible ways of 
settlement of the problems in Transdniestria and the centers 
mostly populated by Gagauz displayed by the Moldovan leadership. 

</TEXT>

