<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tajik Refugees Return Home From Afghanistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tajik Refugees Return Home From Afghanistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205132794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1015 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A group of 480 Tajik refugees returned to their 
homeland from Afghanistan Thursday via a check-point in Nizhny 
Pyanj. 
  INTERFAX was informed by the Tajik parliament's commission 
for refugees that this was the first time in the last three 
weeks that refugees had been sent home. 
  The repatriates are from the Khotlon region (formerly 
Kurgan-Tyube) in southern Tajikistan. 
  The refugees commission said that at least 25,000 Tajik 
refugees are still in Afghanistan. 

</TEXT>

