<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rakhmonov Confirms Decision to Rejoin Ruble Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rakhmonov Confirms Decision to Rejoin Ruble Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305083194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0742 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1305083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by TIA KHOVAR correspondent Abdugaffor Kurbonov for </F>
TASS] 
  [Text] Dushanbe 13 May TASS -- "It can now be said with 
certainty that Tajikistan will rejoin the ruble zone -- the 
country's welfare depends on this first of all. We will build a 
single economic space with Russia," Tajikistan's leader Emomali 
Rakhmonov said at a meeting with local activists in the 
mountainous region of Tajikabad on 12 May. 
  "We discussed these questions with Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin and government chairman Viktor Chernomyrdin," Rakhmonov 
said. 
  At present the heads of government of the two countries are 
busy drafting relevant bilateral agreements to cover all 
economic aspects of the merger -- banking, customs, and taxation. 

</TEXT>

