<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Discusses Niyazov Plan to Encourage Savings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Discusses Niyazov Plan to Encourage Savings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305100194 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0800 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A three-year program for Turkmenistan's 
socioeconomic development was proposed at today's meeting of the 
republican parliament in Ashgabat. Our correspondent says it 
was drafted by President Niyazov. The program is entitled "10 
Years of Prosperity" and contains specific presidential 
proposals. These include, for example, the idea that there 
should be a change in the ratio between the proportion of wages 
devoted to living expenses and the proportion set aside as 
savings. The leaders of contemporary Turkmenistan claim that 
citizens should be able to save 30-40 percent of their income 
and that all the necessary conditions have been created in the 
Republic for this. 

</TEXT>

