<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidium Approves Bills on Civil Defense, Land Code </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidium Approves Bills on Civil Defense, Land Code </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205140994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1120 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 12 TASS -- The bill on the Russian land 
code undoubtedly became the main issue discussed on Thursday by 
the Presidium of the Russian Government. Following numerous 
remarks by ministers and heads of departments, the bill was 
adopted as a whole. 
  A decision was made to submit the land code to the Russian 
Parliament lower chamber on June 2 after it is finalised. 
  "The land code which is still a bill, interferes with 
reforms", Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin summed up speeches on this 
top priority issue for Russia. "The absence of the legislative 
basis retards reforms in the agricultural sector and blocks 
channels for domestic and foreign investors. 
  "On the other hand, we must not leave unsettled issues and 
legal contradictions," the premier stressed. 
  Vice-Premiers Sergey Shakhray and Anatoliy Chubays spoke 
about the above problems when discussing the land code bill. 
They were interested in how members of the Russian Federation 
will behave themselves when the land code is adopted. 
  They also asked why the bill favours the principle of state 
regulation of land relations at the expense of the rights of 
owner, including foreigners. The vice-premiers suggested that 
the document be finalised by the Government without shifting 
this task onto legislators. 
  The Government Presidium also approved the bill on civil 
defence as a whole. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

