<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Killed in Bomb Explosion in Groznyy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Killed in Bomb Explosion in Groznyy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205174994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1404 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An explosion shook a residential area in Chechnya's 
capital, Groznyy, on Tuesday [10 May]. It killed four people 
and injured 10 more. Interfax's correspondents report that an 
armed unit of the Chechen opposition, Ruslan Lobozanov's group, 
is based there. 
  A prominent official from Chechnya's Interior Ministry told 
Interfax that the mine was set by another criminal group for the 
purpose of revenge. It was placed between the 3rd and the 4th 
storeys of a building. The blast claimed the lives of two 
Lobozanov militants and killed two local residents. 
  It is believed that this is a continuation of the events 
that 
took place earlier this year, when nine people died in an armed 
clash between Lobozanov's men and another grouping. Lobozanov's 
gang lost two men in that fire exchange. 
  After Tuesday's blast Lobozanov's men went in the direction 
of their enemy's headquarters. According to the Interior 
Ministry, it is doing its best now to stop the armed conflict 
from getting out of control. 

</TEXT>

