<H3> <TI>   Azeri Troops Reportedly Violate Karabakh Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azeri Troops Reportedly Violate Karabakh Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205105994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1044 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205105994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS corespondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan 12 May TASS -- The Russian and CSCE-brokered 
cease-fire, which was to come into force in Nagorno-Karabakh 
last midnight was violated by Azerbaijani troops on Thursday [12 
May] morning when they tried to break through Karabakh positions 
on the Adgam frontline. 
  According to the Karabakh Army headquarters, the Azerbaijani 
forces were repelled and had to retreat to previous positions. 
  The press department of the enclave reported, quoting 
military sources, that Azerbaijan in concentrating forces to the 
north of the mardakert region of Karabakh. 
  However, it was quiet on the Armenian border overnight and 
in 
the morning. No incidents were registered there, TASS was told 
by the Armenian Defence Ministry. 

</TEXT>

