<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Parliament Addresses Russian State Duma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Parliament Addresses Russian State Duma </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205165994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1625 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 12 May TASS -- "We all are overwhelmed with 
the warmest feelings towards the Russian people and its 
legislators," the Ukrainian newly-elected parliament said in 
today's address to the Russian State Duma. 
  In their address, issued at the parliament's first session, 
Ukrainian lawmakers said they strongly believed in mutual 
understanding and ability of both parliaments to settle 
differences between newly-independent states by means of 
reasonable political bargaining and compromises not infringing 
upon the vital interests of the Russian and Ukrainian peoples. 
  It is noteworthy that Ukrainian lawmakers unanimously agreed 
with the wording of the telegram, but radical nationalists 
demanded that the telegram be written in the Ukrainian language, 
which is still unlikely to change the content of the address. 

</TEXT>

