<H3> <TI>   Six Candidates to Run in Presidential Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Candidates to Run in Presidential Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1205110194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1930 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1205110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Ivan Kyshko, member of the Central Electoral 
Commission for the election of the president of Ukraine, 
informed a UNIAN correspondent on 11 May, (the last day for 
submitting lists of signatures in support of contenders for the 
presidential election) that documents from district electoral 
commissions on the results of collecting signatures have been 
received by the Central Electoral Commission. According to the 
documents, Ivan Plyushch, Leonid Kravchuk, Leonid Kuchma, 
Oleksandr Moroz, Volodymyr Lanovyy, and Petro Talanchuk have 
gathered the required number of signatures (100,000). According 
to Ihor Kyshka, Valeriy Babych, Ivan Valenya, and Mykola Rud, 
who were unable to gather the required number of signatures 
within the established time limit, have withdrawn from the 
election campaign. 
  With regard to the candidacies of Volodymyr Lanovyy and 
Petro 
Talanchuk, the Central Electoral Commission is clarifying 
information concerning the demands of the law on collecting 
1,500 signatures in 18 oblasts. 
  As a UNIAN correspondent learned from informed sources, the 
final number of signatures gathered is as follows: Leonid 
Kravchuk -- 270,000; Leonid Kuchma -- 210,000; Ivan Plyushch -- 
130,000; Petro Talanchuk -- 120,000; Oleksandr Moroz -- 120,000; 
Volodymyr Lanovyy -- 100,000. 

</TEXT>

