<F P=102>   LD1605043094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0403 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605043094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 16 -- The military leaders of Armenia, 
Azerbaijan and Nagorno-Karabakh are meeting in Moscow today to 
compare notes, with the mediation of the Russian Federation, on 
further steps towards the settlement around Karabakh. 
  The CSCE's Minsk conference on Karabakh Jan Eliasson [as 
received] told ITAR-TASS in Moscow that he hopes that the 
forthcoming Moscow meeting will become an important phase in the 
process of the settlement of the Karabakh issue. Eliasson 
called for the participation of international observers in 
ensuring the implementation of the ceasefire accords. The 
mechanism of international verification was in the focus of the 
consultations held by the joint mission of the Conference for 
Security and Cooperation in Europe and Russia in the region. 
  The Russian president's special envoy Vladimir Kazimirov, 
and 
the leaders of Armenia's defence ministry and the Karabakh army 
flew to Moscow from Yerevan on Sunday night to join the 
conference on Monday. 

